abstract String de.unibi.techfak.bibiserv.biodom.RNAStructMLInterface.addToNewRNAStructure (  String  rnasequence,
String  seqId,
String  description,
int  sequenceType,
String  program,
String  command,
String  version,
String  date,
String  comment,
String  shape,
Double  shapeProb,
String  structure,
Double  structProb,
Double  energy
)  throws BioDOMException [pure virtual]
 

This method adds a new rnastructure element to the dom and returns the corrosponding id. several elements can be defined. id both a shape & a structure are supplied, then it is assumed that the structure refers to the shape. You can leave arguments empty : use null ! At least one shape or one structure should be supplied. The function returns the id of the generated rnastructure. This can be used to add additional elements to the structure.

Parameters:
rnasequence - String, should contain only 'A' 'G' 'C' and 'U' chars : The rna sequence
seqId - String, id for the rna sequence
description - String, description for the rna sequence
sequenceType- int, NUCLEIC_SEQUENCE or FREE_SEQUENCE final
program - String, Name of the program used to generate the data
command - String, command used
version - String, version of the program
date - String, date of the program run, format: YYYY-MM-DD
comment - String, comment
shape - String, shape, allowed chars: '[',']','(',')','{','}','<','>' and '_'
shapeProb - Double, probability for the shape
structure - String, structure, allowed chars: '[',']','(',')','{','}','<','>' and '.'
structProb - Double, probability for the structure
energy - Double, energy value for the structure
Returns:
String - id of the generated rnastructure element
Exceptions:
BioDOMException

abstract List<String> de.unibi.techfak.bibiserv.biodom.RNAStructMLInterface.appendFromDotBracketFasta (  Reader  dotbracketFasta  )  throws BioDOMException, IOException [pure virtual]
 

method that appends sequence and structure information to RNAStructML by extracting the data from a DotBracketFasta string. DotBracketFasta must follow the following format rules: >IDSTRING DESCRIPTION SEQUENCESTRING DOTBRACKETSTRING ENERGY(optional) - this line can occurs one or more >IDSTRING2 DESCRIPTION2 SEQUENCESTRING2 DOTBRACKETSTRING2 ENERGY(optional) - this line can occurs one or more

Parameters:
dotbracketFasta - DotBracketFasta Reader, see format above
Returns:
List<String> - Contains the id attributes of all generated rnastructure element in order
Exceptions:
BioDOMException - on error
IOException - on IOError

abstract Hashtable<String, Object> de.unibi.techfak.bibiserv.biodom.RNAStructMLInterface.getSequence (  String  rnastructure_id  )  throws BioDOMException [pure virtual]
 

getter method. returns a Hashtable containing the sequence information. Keys in the Hash are generated only for information items contained in the sequence element! key/values: seqID / String - id of the sequence name / String - name of the sequence synonyms / List<String> - synonyms to the name description / String - description of the sequence sequence / String - the sequence string, this element is not in the Hash, if the sequenceType is EMPTYSEQUENCE sequenceType / Integer - NUCLEIC, FREE or EMPTYSEQUENCE sequenceTypeName / String - NUCLEICSEQUENCE_NAME, FREESEQUENCE_NAME or EMPTYSEQUENCE_NAME comment / String - String with comment

Parameters:
rnastructure_id - id of the rnastructure element
Returns:
Hashtable<String,Object> - contains the sequence information

BioDOMException - on error
